The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning algorithm for adaptive traffic signal control, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves deep learning and neural networks, which are common in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The algorithm is designed to control traffic signals, which is related to robotics and control systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves system optimization and control, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves the use of experience replay and target network mechanisms, which are common in reinforcement learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category.
